President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Massachusetts in response to a severe winter storm, snowstorm, and flooding that occurred in January 2015. This declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs or replacements, snow assistance, and hazard mitigation measures. Mark H. Landry has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.